Peru Stocks: Cerro Verde, Credicorp, Southern Copper Climb

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-10-12T17:06:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/peru-stocks-cerro-verde-credicorp-southern-copper-climb.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:43 a.m. Lima time.  The Lima General Index rose 1.4 percent to 18,532.21. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 2 percent to 2,449.30.  Banking and mining shares advanced as U.S. stocks climbed
and copper gained after the European Union released a roadmap of
its plans to recapitalize banks and halt the euro area’s debt
crisis.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, advanced 4.3 percent to $102.50, the steepest intraday
rise in six weeks. BBVA  Banco Continental SA (CONTINC1)  (CONTINC1 PE), the
local unit of  Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA,
climbed 2.9 percent to 5.40 soles.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest producer of
the metal, rose 4.6 percent to $28.13. Sociedad Minera Cerro
Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), the nation’s third-largest copper
producer, climbed 3.6 percent to $35.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  